    <text>
        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>

            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; portion Emor.
                <date>5613</date><lb/> &#40;ca. <date>April</date>&#41;</p>
            <p>May the mountains and the hills carry peace and blessings with&#8211;<lb/>out end to
                my dear and loyal friend&#44; the accomplished and<lb/> learned&#44; whose name is
                known in the gate of a great city etc.</p>
            <p>Dear Sir and Friend&#44;</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Again I lift up my pen to reveal to you<lb/> that I and the members of my household
                are&#44; thank God&#44; well<lb/> and whole. I hope that you too are also in good
                health&#44; and<lb/> that your spirits will not fail. Now&#44; will you please let
                me<lb/> know the reason why you have been silent. For I have written<lb/> several
                times and have as yet had no word in return. What is<lb/> the reason&#44; and what
                the cause why you turn to me your back<lb/> and not your face. I hope that the
                        <del><add>&#63;</add></del> flame of love<lb/> which used to burn upon the
                altar of friendship&#44; will not be<lb/> extinguished. Therefore&#44; if you want
                to do me honor&#44; please<lb/> reply to me.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Now&#44; will you be good enough to print the<lb/> letter signed by the learned
                gentleman <persName>Abraham Benjamini</persName> who<lb/> was a witness at the time
                when the children of &#8220;Bnai Israel&#8221;<lb/> were picked to stand an
                examination. The other letter is by<lb/> myself about the occasion when the school
                was established to<lb/> teach the Children of Israel &#40;Bnai Israel&#41; to go up
                on the<lb/> highway that leads to the house of God. If you see that my<lb/> words
                are correct and will charm the reader&#44; please recount<lb/> the matter in order.
                The mere printing of the letters will<lb/> achieve much good.<lb/> From your
                well&#8211;wisher and one anxious for<lb/> your affection<del><add>&#63;</add></del>&#44;<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Simon ha&#8211;Cohen Noht</persName><lb/> Cantor and
                preacher of Cong.<lb/> Bnai Israel</p>


        </body>
